{"TopicId":143924,"ForumId":50,"TopicTitle":"Dark Side Transit Formula for Any Orbit","CreatedByName":"blorgon","CreatedById":159569,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-16T11:14:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"blorgon","CreatedById":159569,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-16T11:14:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrently reworking the 3D graphical calculator. Check back soon!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-21T02:15:30Z\u0022 title=\u002207/21/2016 02:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by blorgon\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-18T20:20:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor elliptical orbits, you can find a formula here: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Orbit_darkness_time\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Orbit_darkness_time\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"blorgon","CreatedById":159569,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-18T20:36:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222681544\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143924\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468873218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278756\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mhoram\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, mhoram said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor elliptical orbits, you can find a formula here: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Orbit_darkness_time\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Orbit_darkness_time\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell would you look at that. Google failed me miserably when I was searching for this, so I ended up making my own calculator and coming up with my own formula. Nice to know it exists. Gonna go check my results against this equation now!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"blorgon","CreatedById":159569,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-20T18:50:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222681544\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022143924\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221468873218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278756\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mhoram\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/18/2016 at 2:20 PM, mhoram said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor elliptical orbits, you can find a formula here: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Orbit_darkness_time\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Orbit_darkness_time\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I\u0027ve actually been working on a calculator that will calculate for inclined orbits too. Of course, an orbit whose ellipse is perpendicular to Kerbin\u0027s orbital path and\u00A0with\u00A0a transit whose midpoint is apoapsis will always be the absolute longest transit. But I wanted to work it out anyway.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}